.TH "mdiobus_write" 9 "mdiobus_write" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
mdiobus_write \- Convenience function for writing a given MII mgmt register
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" mdiobus_write
.BI "(struct mii_bus *bus "  ","
.BI "int addr "  ","
.BI "u32 regnum "  ","
.BI "u16 val "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "bus" 12
the mii_bus struct
.IP "addr" 12
the phy address
.IP "regnum" 12
register number to write
.IP "val" 12
value to write to \fIregnum\fP
.SH "NOTE"
MUST NOT be called from interrupt context,
because the bus read/write functions may wait for an interrupt
to conclude the operation.
